What, in degrees, is the measure of the largest angle in $\triangle PQR?$

\begin{center}
    \begin{asy}
    size(8cm);
    draw((0,0)--(-1.3,4)--(7,0)--cycle);
label("$P$",(-1.3,4),NW); label("$Q$",(0,0),SW); label("$R$",(7,0),SE);

label("$6x^\circ$",(0,0),NE); label("$x^\circ$",(5,0),N); label("$3x^\circ$",(-.25,3));
    \end{asy}
\end{center}
}

\textbf{Answer:} Since the sum of the angles in a triangle is $180^\circ,$ then\begin{align*}
3x^\circ + x^\circ + 6x^\circ &= 180^\circ \\
10x &= 180 \\
x & = 18.
\end{align*}The largest angle in the triangle is$$6x^\circ = 6(18^\circ)=\boxed{108}^\circ.$$
}
